        {
            "_id": "hKpURVpYlVxOwvPX",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Compelling Order",
            "sort": 500000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per round</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> Korven barks out an order at a creature within 30 feet, filling his command with humiliating insults and implied threats of punishment if the order is disobeyed, choosing from one of the following commands: \"drop your weapons,\" \"kneel,\" \"stand at attention,\" or \"pledge your loyalty.\" The target must attempt a @Check[will|dc:26] save with the following results, after which it is immune to Compelling Order for 1 minute.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature can ignore the order; doing so causes Korven to sputter and rage, causing him to become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Slowed]{Slowed 1} on his next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature resists the order but takes @Damage[4d6[mental]] damage as it does so.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature is compelled to spend its first action on its next turn following the order, and also takes @Damage[8d6[mental]] damage from the shame.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature is compelled to spend its entire turn following the order, and takes @Damage[16d6[mental]] damage from the shame.</p>"
                },
                "frequency": {
                    "max": 1,
                    "per": "round"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": [
                        "auditory",
                        "divine",
                        "emotion",
                        "linguistic",
                        "mental"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "9seeuDwxECDXIfWY",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Phantom Amputation",
            "sort": 600000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>Each time a creature takes damage in a round from the bloody tendril Strike extending from Korven's wrist, it believes its fingers, hand, or similar appendage has been amputated. The creature must succeed at a @Check[will|dc:26] save or become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Frightened]{Frightened 1} (@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Frightened]{Frightened 2} on a critical failure). If the creature is already frightened, it instead becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 1} for 24 hours on a failed save (or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 2} for 24 hours on critical failure).</p>"
                },
